Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: COURT ORDERED DEFENDANT REMANDED TO THE JUDGE ON RETURN OF THE BENCH WARRANT.

Attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke in court.  Stephanie Krueger appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Case in court for calendar call.  Defendant failing to appear, Court ordered a bench warrant to be issued with REMAND TO JUDGE upon return of the bench warrant. Court took no action on bail.

Attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke in court.  Stephanie Krueger appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
CASE HELD OFF THE RECORD PER JUDGE.  Case in court for scheduling conference. Defendant does not appear. Court unable to hear matter at scheduled time.  Court set a calendar call date.  Case adjourned to Branch 40.  Calendar call scheduled for August 12, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant James Vongsoury in court with attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke.  Defendant James Vongsoury in custody.  Abby Rockendorf appeared in person for the State of Wisconsin.  PARTIES APPEAR BY VIDEO.
Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the State: West Allis Officer M. Lazaris.   State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty.  Case is adjourned to Branch 40.  Scheduling conference scheduled for August 8, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant James Vongsoury in court with attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke appear by video.  Defendant James Vongsoury in custody.  Annie Louk appeared in person for the State of Wisconsin. Case set for a preliminary hearing. State witness present. Attorney needs more time to meet with client.
Court ordered case adjourned for CAUSE for a Preliminary Hearing in Preliminary Hearing Court, Room 146 of the Criminal Justice Facility.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for June 2, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Court ordered Justice Point Pretrial Services LEVEL 2 SUPERVISION.  Court reminders.  No driving without a valid license.  Defendant advised if released from custody it is a requirement to attend all future court proceedings.  Failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping, a warrant issued or high cash bail.

Defendant James Vongsoury in court with attorney Ruby De Leon.  Defendant James Vongsoury in custody.  John E. Flynn appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  James Vongsoury appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Shelton, Branch 40. Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold the defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  This hearing will be streamed live on Dacast:  https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/99073afd-37c2-acfa-830d-b1ddcaebf0ea  Preliminary hearing scheduled for May 12, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
